The paper discusses current threat modeling approaches and proposes a new approach that considers attack characteristics and attacker environment. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of game theory, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed approach also involves analyzing attack phases and limitations, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and system identification (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the unrealistic assumptions made in current threat modeling, which is relevant to cybersecurity (cs.CY).
